1
00:00:01,598 --> 00:00:02,889
Solar.

2
00:00:02,889 --> 00:00:04,911
Are you going to take medicine to sleep?

3
00:00:05,533 --> 00:00:09,515
Do we really need to rush
and push him out of our lives like this?

4
00:00:09,515 --> 00:00:12,464
I can feel
that he's not okay with this at all.

5
00:00:12,464 --> 00:00:16,550
I probably didn't wake up on our anniversary.

6
00:00:16,550 --> 00:00:17,761
Is that a music CD?

7
00:00:17,761 --> 00:00:18,824
Play it for me, please.

8
00:00:18,824 --> 00:00:20,392
Hey, Sun!

9
00:00:20,392 --> 00:00:21,817
Who knows?

10
00:00:21,817 --> 00:00:25,945
Your song might just be the thing
that helps Sun turn into Solar faster.

11
00:00:25,945 --> 00:00:28,109
Can I cuddle you all night?

12
00:00:56,168 --> 00:00:57,476
Yes!

13
00:00:57,476 --> 00:00:59,614
There! He's fallen asleep!

14
00:01:00,395 --> 00:01:02,715
I'm not asleep yet!

15
00:01:05,805 --> 00:01:08,408
What are you doing, uncles and auntie?

16
00:01:08,408 --> 00:01:10,726
Why are you making me watch this guitar clip?

17
00:01:14,075 --> 00:01:15,181
Just go.

18
00:01:15,181 --> 00:01:18,610
Go. It's time for class.

19
00:01:24,815 --> 00:01:26,793
But I want to know.

20
00:01:27,979 --> 00:01:29,300
Here.

21
00:01:29,300 --> 00:01:31,412
I'm giving you this, so tell me.

22
00:01:33,799 --> 00:01:35,127
Here.

23
00:01:35,127 --> 00:01:37,485
I'm giving you this
so I don't have to tell you.

24
00:01:37,485 --> 00:01:38,991
Go!

25
00:01:38,991 --> 00:01:40,791
Hurry up!

26
00:01:48,293 --> 00:01:51,615
Looks like just playing any clip won't work.

27
00:01:52,393 --> 00:01:54,799
How about you guys take the CD
to a repair shop?

28
00:01:54,799 --> 00:01:57,183
At this point, I think it's ready.

29
00:01:57,183 --> 00:01:59,900
- Ready to be fixed?
- Ready for a memorial service

30
00:01:59,900 --> 00:02:03,921
for the CD that was once our hope,
now gone from us.

31
00:02:05,007 --> 00:02:06,893
Why does this always happen to me?

32
00:02:06,893 --> 00:02:08,332
Come on.

33
00:02:08,332 --> 00:02:10,213
Don't lose hope just yet.

34
00:02:10,213 --> 00:02:11,604
At least you still have me.

35
00:02:11,604 --> 00:02:13,320
You still have Sodchuen.

36
00:02:13,320 --> 00:02:15,550
We're always here to support you.

37
00:02:17,794 --> 00:02:20,175
But for now, let's head to the meeting.

38
00:02:20,175 --> 00:02:23,729
I have something urgent
to announce to all the teachers.

39
00:03:42,484 --> 00:03:47,387
And finally... it's that time of year again.

40
00:03:47,387 --> 00:03:52,225
The day teachers like us
wish would never come.

41
00:03:53,188 --> 00:03:55,752
What day is she talking about, Jee?

42
00:03:55,752 --> 00:03:56,839
How would I know?

43
00:03:56,839 --> 00:03:58,639
That is...

44
00:04:00,547 --> 00:04:04,492
Class Play Day from the English department!

45
00:04:08,815 --> 00:04:12,550
I've called this meeting today

46
00:04:12,550 --> 00:04:16,550
because I want to hear all of your opinions.

47
00:04:16,550 --> 00:04:19,220
Since Teacher Solar isn't well,

48
00:04:19,220 --> 00:04:23,080
how should we handle Grade 2 Class 1?

49
00:04:23,080 --> 00:04:25,366
Can't we just cancel it?

50
00:04:25,366 --> 00:04:29,995
No! I will never let a tragedy
like last year happen again!

51
00:04:29,995 --> 00:04:31,359
A tragedy?

52
00:04:31,359 --> 00:04:33,370
What tragedy?

53
00:04:35,882 --> 00:04:39,479
That day should've been an ordinary day

54
00:04:39,479 --> 00:04:43,647
for a little girl who had just become
the new principal.

55
00:04:43,647 --> 00:04:45,447
Alas...

56
00:04:47,440 --> 00:04:49,000
[Justice For Our Play!]
[The Play! The Play! The Play!]

57
00:04:51,074 --> 00:04:54,920
She completely forgot
she had to organize the class play.

58
00:04:54,920 --> 00:04:58,320
Give us back our play!
[Justice For Our Play!]

59
00:04:58,560 --> 00:05:02,080
Give us back our play!

60
00:05:02,080 --> 00:05:05,408
Give us back our play!
[No Play, No Us!]

61
00:05:05,408 --> 00:05:08,341
Give us back our play!
[The Play! The Play! The Play!]

62
00:05:08,341 --> 00:05:09,604
- Help!
- Give us back our play!

63
00:05:09,604 --> 00:05:11,411
Help me!

64
00:05:12,358 --> 00:05:13,441
So...

65
00:05:13,441 --> 00:05:15,436
does anyone want to volunteer

66
00:05:15,436 --> 00:05:18,698
to take care of that class
instead of Teacher Solar?

67
00:05:27,320 --> 00:05:31,810
Well, can I take care of Solar's class?

68
00:05:39,430 --> 00:05:40,576
Oh!

69
00:05:40,576 --> 00:05:41,778
Teacher Pobmek!

70
00:05:41,778 --> 00:05:44,145
You're being funny.

71
00:05:44,145 --> 00:05:46,265
I'm not.

72
00:05:46,265 --> 00:05:52,235
If it's for Teacher Solar, I'll do anything.

73
00:05:52,235 --> 00:05:56,267
Teacher Pobmek, this is serious.

74
00:05:56,267 --> 00:05:58,372
- Are you sure you're up for it?
- I am.

75
00:05:58,372 --> 00:06:00,200
Let me be honest.

76
00:06:00,200 --> 00:06:02,170
I don't believe you.

77
00:06:02,170 --> 00:06:04,569
And I'm not comfortable with that.

78
00:06:04,569 --> 00:06:08,598
So let's have Teacher Jee help you out.

79
00:06:08,598 --> 00:06:10,419
Happy to help.

80
00:06:11,113 --> 00:06:12,520
Everyone, please don't forget...

81
00:06:12,520 --> 00:06:13,689
[Important: Record every kid's performance!]

82
00:06:13,689 --> 00:06:17,257
Take videos and send to their parents.
[Parents' request!]

83
00:06:17,257 --> 00:06:22,048
And please refer to this schedule
for more details.

84
00:06:22,048 --> 00:06:27,043
Most importantly, first,
we'll have the kids choose a director.

85
00:06:27,043 --> 00:06:31,513
Then we'll let
the little director take it from there.

86
00:06:31,513 --> 00:06:32,920
Okay.

87
00:06:32,920 --> 00:06:35,662
As long as the kids don't choose Sun
as the director,

88
00:06:35,662 --> 00:06:37,704
it should be easy.

89
00:06:38,705 --> 00:06:41,284
If anyone has any questions...

90
00:06:41,284 --> 00:06:43,149
Won't Sun sulk?

91
00:06:43,149 --> 00:06:45,623
- Feel free to ask them now.
- Please.

92
00:06:45,623 --> 00:06:47,332
He won't.

93
00:06:47,332 --> 00:06:52,007
We can just give him a lollipop
to keep him quiet.

94
00:06:52,007 --> 00:06:54,905
Sun is so easy to trick.

95
00:07:07,350 --> 00:07:10,938
So our director this year is Sun.

96
00:07:10,938 --> 00:07:14,155
Yay!

97
00:07:16,865 --> 00:07:20,121
Sun! What have you done?

98
00:07:21,010 --> 00:07:23,969
Guys, pick me as your director.

99
00:07:23,969 --> 00:07:27,236
I think we should do Avengers.
The fighting will be fun.

100
00:07:27,236 --> 00:07:28,828
Ew, no.

101
00:07:28,828 --> 00:07:31,125
Guys always go for fighting and violence.

102
00:07:31,125 --> 00:07:34,546
I think Snow White is better.

103
00:07:34,546 --> 00:07:36,725
It's a legendary classic.

104
00:07:36,725 --> 00:07:40,181
Gosh, Elsa! What era are you from?

105
00:07:40,181 --> 00:07:42,879
Snow White is ancient!

106
00:07:42,879 --> 00:07:43,975
If it were really that old,

107
00:07:43,975 --> 00:07:45,760
they wouldn't have made
a live-action version.

108
00:07:45,760 --> 00:07:46,895
- No!
- Avengers is better!

109
00:07:46,895 --> 00:07:48,278
Avengers is better!

110
00:07:48,278 --> 00:07:50,078
Snow White!

111
00:07:51,541 --> 00:07:53,736
Avengers is better!

112
00:07:56,887 --> 00:08:01,710
I think
both Elsa's and King's ideas sound fun.

113
00:08:01,710 --> 00:08:05,733
But to make it even more fun,
you should choose me as your director.

114
00:08:06,628 --> 00:08:08,158
Huh?

115
00:08:08,158 --> 00:08:09,547
Why?

116
00:08:09,547 --> 00:08:13,995
Because I'm going
to do Snow White and the Seven Avengers!

117
00:08:15,767 --> 00:08:20,205
Sun for director!

118
00:08:20,205 --> 00:08:21,933
Trust me! Trust me!

119
00:08:21,933 --> 00:08:23,933
Sun for director!

120
00:08:27,313 --> 00:08:31,496
Well... students, I think...

121
00:08:31,496 --> 00:08:34,958
Sun might not be a good fit for director,

122
00:08:34,958 --> 00:08:37,771
since he can only come to school
every other day.

123
00:08:37,771 --> 00:08:39,516
The rehearsals aren't going to work, right?

124
00:08:39,516 --> 00:08:40,552
Yeah.

125
00:08:40,552 --> 00:08:41,758
It's okay, teachers.

126
00:08:41,758 --> 00:08:44,829
We're professionals.

127
00:08:44,829 --> 00:08:48,389
Besides, everyone's already voted for Sun.

128
00:08:48,389 --> 00:08:52,031
Yes! Yes! Yes!

129
00:08:55,184 --> 00:08:56,694
What are you going to do?

130
00:08:56,694 --> 00:08:59,701
No! We can't let Sun be the director!

131
00:08:59,701 --> 00:09:01,832
Will the kids be okay with that?

132
00:09:07,640 --> 00:09:08,600
[Director = Sun]

133
00:09:08,600 --> 00:09:09,640
[Justice for Sun]

134
00:09:09,832 --> 00:09:19,689
Sun for director!

135
00:09:27,521 --> 00:09:29,431
Here.

136
00:09:29,431 --> 00:09:31,824
This is to keep you quiet, Uncle.

137
00:09:32,946 --> 00:09:35,721
I'll do my best as the director.

138
00:09:37,053 --> 00:09:44,772
Sun for director!

139
00:09:46,031 --> 00:09:47,146
What do you want to play?

140
00:09:47,146 --> 00:09:49,307
What is it again? Snow White?

141
00:09:49,307 --> 00:09:50,926
You want to play her?

142
00:10:09,580 --> 00:10:11,387
Hey.

143
00:10:11,387 --> 00:10:13,440
How's it going?

144
00:10:13,440 --> 00:10:14,860
Nothing much.

145
00:10:14,860 --> 00:10:17,139
The kids are rehearsing the play.

146
00:10:17,139 --> 00:10:19,844
I just got the brief for the set.

147
00:10:22,480 --> 00:10:24,867
Maybe it's not as bad as we thought?

148
00:10:24,867 --> 00:10:31,080
Hey, I'm usually optimistic,
but look at this.

149
00:10:31,080 --> 00:10:32,678
[Snow White and the Seven Avengers]

150
00:10:32,678 --> 00:10:35,166
This is the brief I got.

151
00:10:35,166 --> 00:10:38,006
Do you think we can get it done
in this lifetime?

152
00:10:40,000 --> 00:10:42,000
I'll handle it.

153
00:10:43,373 --> 00:10:45,053
Hey, that's an invader!

154
00:10:45,760 --> 00:10:49,987
Attack!

155
00:10:49,987 --> 00:10:51,433
Hey!

156
00:10:51,433 --> 00:10:53,320
What are you guys doing?

157
00:10:53,960 --> 00:10:56,093
Teacher Pobmek?

158
00:10:56,093 --> 00:10:59,720
Oh, I thought the class next door was coming
to copy our ideas.

159
00:10:59,720 --> 00:11:02,146
Let's get back to the meeting. Come on!

160
00:11:11,527 --> 00:11:13,065
Sorry.

161
00:11:13,847 --> 00:11:16,233
I forgot to warn you about that.

162
00:11:17,173 --> 00:11:21,033
The play is definitely going to be a mess.

163
00:11:30,347 --> 00:11:33,380
"Which mannerly devotion shows in this;

164
00:11:33,380 --> 00:11:37,238
For saints have hands
that pilgrims' hands do touch,

165
00:11:39,139 --> 00:11:44,149
And palm to palm is holy Palmers' kiss."

166
00:11:45,079 --> 00:11:49,188
"Have not saints lips..."

167
00:11:49,188 --> 00:11:50,735
You look confused.

168
00:11:50,735 --> 00:11:51,841
Do you want to start over?

169
00:11:51,841 --> 00:11:52,905
Come on!

170
00:11:52,905 --> 00:11:56,508
No! What are you even making me do?

171
00:11:56,508 --> 00:11:58,308
What?

172
00:11:59,036 --> 00:12:02,167
Hey! Help me.

173
00:12:02,167 --> 00:12:04,168
Please.

174
00:12:04,168 --> 00:12:07,360
You know my scene partner and I
haven't even rehearsed together,

175
00:12:07,360 --> 00:12:09,840
and my exam is today.

176
00:12:11,724 --> 00:12:14,003
Can't we do a simple scene?

177
00:12:14,003 --> 00:12:17,064
Like sitting next to each other,
watching birds, trees, or fish. Anything!

178
00:12:17,064 --> 00:12:19,624
But I have to do the scene
where they first meet.

179
00:12:19,624 --> 00:12:22,815
- No.
- Pretty please.

180
00:12:22,815 --> 00:12:25,092
Please.

181
00:12:25,092 --> 00:12:28,232
Please, or you won't get any sleep.
I'll keep bothering you like this.

182
00:12:28,232 --> 00:12:31,194
Please!

183
00:12:31,194 --> 00:12:33,024
Fine!

184
00:12:33,024 --> 00:12:34,658
Come on.

185
00:12:36,019 --> 00:12:38,491
You're a sweet roommate.

186
00:12:38,491 --> 00:12:40,291
Come on.

187
00:12:49,078 --> 00:12:51,170
Let's put our masks on slowly.

188
00:12:57,101 --> 00:13:00,545
Both walk around,
taking in the atmosphere of the ball.

189
00:13:01,427 --> 00:13:04,368
They're not paying attention
to anyone in particular,

190
00:13:04,368 --> 00:13:09,336
until their eyes slowly meet.

191
00:13:14,089 --> 00:13:16,841
Their gazes are drawn to each other,

192
00:13:18,361 --> 00:13:20,705
looking at each other,

193
00:13:20,705 --> 00:13:23,156
the way you look at someone you like.

194
00:13:45,113 --> 00:13:48,535
We can just angle it.
No need to actually kiss.

195
00:13:51,446 --> 00:13:54,522
What if I actually want to kiss you?

196
00:13:58,152 --> 00:13:59,952
Do you dare?

197
00:14:15,121 --> 00:14:16,504
Shit!

198
00:14:16,504 --> 00:14:18,296
It's time for the exam!

199
00:14:18,296 --> 00:14:19,951
I have to go!

200
00:14:19,951 --> 00:14:22,784
You really helped me with the rehearsal!
Thank you!

201
00:14:52,251 --> 00:14:55,942
Solar, did you forget something?

202
00:14:58,816 --> 00:15:02,138
Oh, I don't need it anymore.

203
00:15:02,777 --> 00:15:05,455
Oh? Why?

204
00:15:09,895 --> 00:15:14,305
My rehearsal partner
forgot the exam was today,

205
00:15:14,305 --> 00:15:16,750
and went to a camp out of town,

206
00:15:18,914 --> 00:15:21,810
so I ended up without a partner.

207
00:15:33,754 --> 00:15:37,236
Let me ask around if anyone else
is doing the same scene as you.

208
00:15:44,470 --> 00:15:46,723
Hey...

209
00:15:46,723 --> 00:15:49,024
Why don't you be my rehearsal partner?

210
00:15:49,835 --> 00:15:52,404
Huh? Me?

211
00:16:09,932 --> 00:16:11,993
What's with that frown
so early in the morning?

212
00:16:12,659 --> 00:16:14,508
What's wrong?

213
00:16:14,508 --> 00:16:19,976
Well, yesterday we started
rehearsing the class play.

214
00:16:19,976 --> 00:16:22,049
Sun was chosen as the director.

215
00:16:24,383 --> 00:16:25,293
Seriously?

216
00:16:25,293 --> 00:16:30,476
Jee and I tried to stop him
from being the director,

217
00:16:30,476 --> 00:16:33,242
but he somehow got hyped up
and just went for it.

218
00:16:33,242 --> 00:16:35,138
Are we going to survive?

219
00:16:51,142 --> 00:16:53,040
Do you remember this?

220
00:16:59,170 --> 00:17:04,471
Then you know how much
both Sun and I are into acting.

221
00:17:08,390 --> 00:17:13,063
Just let the kids work on it.

222
00:17:13,063 --> 00:17:17,245
Your job is just to watch from afar.

223
00:17:17,245 --> 00:17:19,245
Trust Little Sun.

224
00:17:22,401 --> 00:17:27,438
I really want to know
how Director Sun's play will turn out.

225
00:17:33,520 --> 00:17:34,548
[Play Rehearsal]

226
00:17:34,548 --> 00:17:36,655
And action!

227
00:17:36,655 --> 00:17:40,105
Who... Who are you?

228
00:17:40,907 --> 00:17:43,450
I am Snow White.

229
00:17:44,197 --> 00:17:45,837
Snap your fingers!

230
00:17:49,916 --> 00:17:51,934
Squirm more!

231
00:17:51,934 --> 00:17:53,854
Squirm harder!

232
00:17:55,055 --> 00:17:57,848
Yes! Squirm more! Harder!

233
00:17:57,848 --> 00:18:00,219
Go harder! Squirm more!

234
00:18:09,371 --> 00:18:11,358
Whoa.

235
00:18:11,358 --> 00:18:14,528
Is this for an elementary school play,
or Rachadalai Theatre?

236
00:18:15,251 --> 00:18:17,922
I'm relieved to hear that.

237
00:18:17,922 --> 00:18:21,333
I was so worried about how it'd turn out.

238
00:18:21,333 --> 00:18:23,573
Please make it turn out well.

239
00:18:23,573 --> 00:18:26,520
I'm tired of arguing with the parents

240
00:18:26,520 --> 00:18:28,910
and explaining where the school budget went.

241
00:18:33,895 --> 00:18:37,283
Principal, that's not the right way to paint.

242
00:18:37,283 --> 00:18:39,120
Let me show you.

243
00:18:40,818 --> 00:18:42,665
You should do it like this.

244
00:18:42,665 --> 00:18:44,864
I was doing it just like you, wasn't I?

245
00:18:44,864 --> 00:18:46,290
No.

246
00:18:46,290 --> 00:18:49,897
You have to do it exactly like I do,
so the colors will be perfect.

247
00:18:49,897 --> 00:18:52,476
I'm the principal!

248
00:18:52,476 --> 00:18:55,151
Feel free to take a break, Principal.

249
00:19:02,043 --> 00:19:04,622
The set needs to be done next week,

250
00:19:04,622 --> 00:19:07,102
not next academic year.

251
00:19:11,072 --> 00:19:12,382
Oh.

252
00:19:12,382 --> 00:19:14,656
Tinker Bell, Four, is everything alright?

253
00:19:14,656 --> 00:19:17,251
Teacher Pobmek, Sun and Elsa are fighting.

254
00:19:17,251 --> 00:19:18,956
- What?
- What?

255
00:19:33,899 --> 00:19:36,691
Sun, what have you done now?

256
00:19:36,691 --> 00:19:39,195
You caused trouble again, didn't you?

257
00:19:39,195 --> 00:19:41,535
Pobmek, calm down.

258
00:19:41,535 --> 00:19:43,728
Let's listen to the kids first.

259
00:19:47,110 --> 00:19:51,120
Kids, what's going on?

260
00:19:51,120 --> 00:19:54,221
Elsa wants to play Snow White,

261
00:19:54,221 --> 00:19:58,495
but Sun already picked Aurora for the role.

262
00:19:58,495 --> 00:20:01,543
So Elsa said Aurora isn't pretty,

263
00:20:01,543 --> 00:20:03,412
and doesn't deserve to play the lead.

264
00:20:03,412 --> 00:20:08,706
Then Sun said Elsa isn't pretty either,
and Elsa cried.

265
00:20:11,759 --> 00:20:13,136
You caused trouble again.

266
00:20:13,136 --> 00:20:14,858
Elsa started it.

267
00:20:14,858 --> 00:20:17,195
- Weren't you listening, Uncle?
- I was!

268
00:20:17,195 --> 00:20:20,657
But you're the one who made things worse,
weren't you?

269
00:20:20,657 --> 00:20:23,613
You're the director,
so you should talk to your friends nicely,

270
00:20:23,613 --> 00:20:26,099
not scold her and make her cry.

271
00:20:26,099 --> 00:20:28,947
What about you?
You don't even talk to me nicely.

272
00:20:30,951 --> 00:20:32,926
Okay.

273
00:20:32,926 --> 00:20:38,532
As the play supervisor,
I'm removing Sun as director.

274
00:20:42,309 --> 00:20:44,610
You're mean, Uncle.

275
00:20:44,610 --> 00:20:46,558
I hate you so much.

276
00:20:51,479 --> 00:20:54,812
Pobmek, do you really want to do this?

277
00:21:08,461 --> 00:21:10,433
How much longer are you going to sulk?

278
00:21:10,433 --> 00:21:12,438
It's your own fault!

279
00:21:16,395 --> 00:21:19,728
Open the door! I haven't showered yet!

280
00:21:26,473 --> 00:21:28,120
Fine!

281
00:21:28,120 --> 00:21:29,424
Sulk all you want!

282
00:21:29,424 --> 00:21:31,613
You'll snap out of it eventually!

283
00:21:41,369 --> 00:21:44,887
Do I really have to shower
with the water from the dish washing sink?

284
00:21:45,320 --> 00:21:47,560
[Sukhum Udom Rak School]
Darn!

285
00:21:47,975 --> 00:21:50,200
I can't take it anymore!

286
00:21:50,200 --> 00:21:52,151
Come on.

287
00:21:52,151 --> 00:21:55,545
Will there ever be a day
when you don't complain at all?

288
00:22:03,798 --> 00:22:06,316
What did you do?
Why does your hair smell weird?

289
00:22:06,316 --> 00:22:08,947
I used the dish washing liquid
to wash my hair.

290
00:22:14,248 --> 00:22:15,492
Hey.

291
00:22:15,492 --> 00:22:18,141
Pay attention to me!

292
00:22:18,141 --> 00:22:21,637
Give me a second. Aurora's mom is calling.

293
00:22:28,028 --> 00:22:29,539
Hello?

294
00:22:36,047 --> 00:22:37,693
Hey, Jee!

295
00:22:37,693 --> 00:22:39,433
What are you doing?

296
00:22:39,433 --> 00:22:41,273
Look at this.

297
00:22:44,219 --> 00:22:45,834
Ready?

298
00:22:49,160 --> 00:22:50,473
What do you think?

299
00:22:50,473 --> 00:22:52,600
- Isn't it cool?
- Gosh!

300
00:22:52,600 --> 00:22:56,810
Can you just make a simple set
and help me look after the kids?

301
00:22:56,810 --> 00:22:57,933
Sure.

302
00:22:57,933 --> 00:23:00,019
But let me finish this first.

303
00:23:00,019 --> 00:23:02,012
- Just give me four...
- Four hours?

304
00:23:02,012 --> 00:23:03,846
Four days, man!

305
00:23:08,939 --> 00:23:10,739
Hey.

306
00:23:12,279 --> 00:23:15,947
Aurora's mom said Aurora is sick,
and needs to take the day off.

307
00:23:15,947 --> 00:23:17,707
If she doesn't come to school tomorrow,

308
00:23:17,707 --> 00:23:19,160
I'm going to visit her at her house.

309
00:23:19,160 --> 00:23:20,200
Hold on.

310
00:23:20,200 --> 00:23:23,246
Aren't you waking up as Sun tomorrow?

311
00:23:27,680 --> 00:23:29,640
[Teacher Solar & Teacher Pobmek]

312
00:23:40,420 --> 00:23:41,820
Solar.

313
00:23:42,527 --> 00:23:44,620
Are you really not going to sleep?

314
00:23:44,620 --> 00:23:46,499
Will you be okay?

315
00:23:46,499 --> 00:23:48,520
Of course.

316
00:23:48,520 --> 00:23:50,619
I'm worried about Aurora.

317
00:23:51,667 --> 00:23:53,893
It's just one night. I'll be fine.

318
00:23:54,846 --> 00:23:56,973
Okay.

319
00:23:56,973 --> 00:23:59,273
Then I'm staying up with you tonight.

320
00:24:31,499 --> 00:24:33,320
What are you doing?

321
00:24:34,800 --> 00:24:36,620
Keeping you awake.

322
00:24:36,620 --> 00:24:39,486
But you always fall asleep before me.

323
00:24:39,486 --> 00:24:41,393
You're exaggerating.

324
00:24:41,393 --> 00:24:43,733
We've stayed up till morning before.

325
00:24:45,800 --> 00:24:48,120
That was when we were students.

326
00:24:48,120 --> 00:24:49,953
We're still students.

327
00:24:49,953 --> 00:24:51,627
What subject?

328
00:24:51,627 --> 00:24:53,593
Love.

329
00:24:53,593 --> 00:24:57,226
What an uncle joke.
Did you borrow that from your dad?

330
00:25:08,212 --> 00:25:10,340
You're really going for it, huh?

331
00:25:14,113 --> 00:25:18,233
But you have to promise
you won't fall asleep.

332
00:25:26,013 --> 00:25:28,106
You're supposed to pinky promise.

333
00:25:28,106 --> 00:25:30,560
Come on. I'm not falling asleep!

334
00:25:41,320 --> 00:25:43,880
[Aurora's Mom]

335
00:25:53,600 --> 00:25:55,400
Hello?

336
00:25:58,340 --> 00:26:00,063
Got it, Ma'am.

337
00:26:06,527 --> 00:26:08,853
I accidentally fell asleep.

338
00:26:10,453 --> 00:26:14,120
How did you even stay up?
You're not sleepy?

339
00:26:18,453 --> 00:26:22,320
Oh, by the way, Aurora's mom just called.

340
00:26:22,320 --> 00:26:25,639
Aurora's taking another sick day.

341
00:26:25,639 --> 00:26:30,935
I already called Sodchuen
and asked to be a bit late,

342
00:26:30,935 --> 00:26:32,846
so we can go visit Aurora.

343
00:26:42,179 --> 00:26:44,127
Aurora,

344
00:26:44,127 --> 00:26:46,526
why have you been missing school
for the past two days?

345
00:26:46,526 --> 00:26:47,900
Are you sick?

346
00:26:47,900 --> 00:26:50,873
Yes, I'm sick.

347
00:26:55,899 --> 00:27:00,026
Or are you skipping school
because you're fighting with Elsa?

348
00:27:00,026 --> 00:27:01,800
No, Teacher!

349
00:27:01,800 --> 00:27:06,433
Oh? Then why do you look fine?

350
00:27:13,327 --> 00:27:17,686
Well, the other day,
I fell and sprained my leg,

351
00:27:17,686 --> 00:27:22,040
but I don't want anyone to know I'm weak.

352
00:27:38,580 --> 00:27:42,426
But your friends are waiting to see you.

353
00:27:43,413 --> 00:27:49,200
I want to see them too, especially Elsa.

354
00:27:49,200 --> 00:27:52,673
But why didn't you say anything back to her
the other day?

355
00:27:52,673 --> 00:27:59,373
Well, Elsa was already sad enough
about not getting the lead role.

356
00:27:59,373 --> 00:28:03,640
I didn't want to hurt her even more.

357
00:28:06,792 --> 00:28:10,560
That's my lead girl!

358
00:28:10,560 --> 00:28:12,360
- Huh?
- Huh?

359
00:28:13,706 --> 00:28:15,506
You're Sun?

360
00:28:19,426 --> 00:28:21,653
Teacher Pobmek...

361
00:28:21,653 --> 00:28:25,393
About Elsa, Sun didn't do anything wrong.

362
00:28:25,393 --> 00:28:28,699
He just wanted to protect me.

363
00:28:28,699 --> 00:28:34,360
So, could you please let Sun
direct the play again?

364
00:28:42,867 --> 00:28:44,667
Alright.

365
00:28:46,266 --> 00:28:50,806
But you have to promise
you'll do your best.

366
00:28:50,806 --> 00:28:53,640
Sure. I promise.

367
00:29:04,033 --> 00:29:05,527
What should we do with the branch?

368
00:29:05,527 --> 00:29:07,587
Like this.

369
00:29:07,587 --> 00:29:09,546
Hey, don't tease her.

370
00:29:09,546 --> 00:29:11,346
That's it!

371
00:29:17,220 --> 00:29:18,593
Are you ready, kids?

372
00:29:18,593 --> 00:29:21,780
Yes, we are!

373
00:29:21,780 --> 00:29:26,087
Three... Two... One!

374
00:29:36,440 --> 00:29:39,520
[Snow White and the Seven Avengers]

375
00:29:39,520 --> 00:29:40,913
Finally!

376
00:29:40,913 --> 00:29:43,746
The play is today!

377
00:29:47,273 --> 00:29:48,580
I know.

378
00:29:48,580 --> 00:29:50,093
What, Uncle?

379
00:29:50,093 --> 00:29:51,267
Aren't you excited?

380
00:29:51,267 --> 00:29:56,040
Forget excited. I'm not even awake yet!

381
00:29:58,900 --> 00:30:01,006
Pobmek!

382
00:30:01,006 --> 00:30:02,373
We're in trouble!

383
00:30:02,373 --> 00:30:04,173
Huh?

384
00:30:13,873 --> 00:30:15,713
What is this?

385
00:30:18,000 --> 00:30:19,800
I'm sorry.

386
00:30:23,006 --> 00:30:26,193
Sodchuen, what happened?

387
00:30:26,193 --> 00:30:27,886
It's that guy.

388
00:30:27,886 --> 00:30:29,706
He went up to fix the broken light,

389
00:30:29,706 --> 00:30:31,966
but the scaffolding collapsed
and smashed the set.

390
00:30:31,966 --> 00:30:33,720
It's completely ruined.

391
00:30:33,720 --> 00:30:37,139
I get that it's an accident...

392
00:30:38,400 --> 00:30:40,881
but we spent a whole week building it,

393
00:30:40,881 --> 00:30:43,233
and it came crashing down in one day!

394
00:30:57,307 --> 00:31:00,640
Teacher Pobmek, what should we do now?

395
00:31:10,567 --> 00:31:16,646
Sun, how about we postpone the play?

396
00:31:29,620 --> 00:31:30,860
Sun!

397
00:31:30,860 --> 00:31:32,033
Sun, where are you going?

398
00:31:32,033 --> 00:31:33,833
Sun!

399
00:31:40,346 --> 00:31:42,333
Sun, what are you doing?

400
00:31:42,333 --> 00:31:45,226
Uncle, please take these to Teacher Jee.

401
00:31:52,300 --> 00:31:54,140
Auntie, what are you daydreaming about?

402
00:31:54,140 --> 00:31:56,867
Hey! I'm the principal!

403
00:31:56,867 --> 00:31:59,953
Yes. Help me out, Principal. Please.

404
00:32:05,253 --> 00:32:06,713
Let me grab some more, just in case.

405
00:32:06,713 --> 00:32:08,966
What are we going to use these for?

406
00:32:19,520 --> 00:32:21,926
Little Sun, what are you doing?

407
00:32:21,926 --> 00:32:23,786
Painting, of course.

408
00:32:26,033 --> 00:32:29,153
Does anyone have a handkerchief I can use?

409
00:32:31,392 --> 00:32:33,980
Hey! Teacher Pobmek!

410
00:32:33,980 --> 00:32:39,259
Teacher Jee, you'd do anything
to make it turn out perfect, right?

411
00:32:39,259 --> 00:32:42,266
Of course! Why?

412
00:32:46,040 --> 00:32:47,600
[Class 2/1]

413
00:32:47,600 --> 00:32:48,773
Yes, sir.

414
00:32:48,773 --> 00:32:51,460
I definitely won't forget
to take videos of your kid.

415
00:32:51,460 --> 00:32:53,420
Okay, bye.

416
00:33:05,093 --> 00:33:07,033
Snow White and the Seven Avengers.

417
00:33:07,033 --> 00:33:09,393
And action!

418
00:33:12,007 --> 00:33:14,586
Once upon a time in the forest,

419
00:33:14,586 --> 00:33:19,813
there lived a kind and gentle girl
named Snow White!

420
00:33:34,713 --> 00:33:37,586
Wow!

421
00:33:39,393 --> 00:33:41,320
Wow!

422
00:33:41,320 --> 00:33:45,873
Snow White was about to meet
the Seven Avengers!

423
00:33:52,967 --> 00:33:55,693
Whoa!

424
00:34:07,119 --> 00:34:10,540
Sun, where did Elsa go?

425
00:34:10,540 --> 00:34:12,033
Is she not playing the tree anymore?

426
00:34:12,033 --> 00:34:13,933
She didn't go anywhere.

427
00:34:15,426 --> 00:34:17,439
She just changed roles.

428
00:34:30,813 --> 00:34:35,753
Aurora, I'm sorry
for saying you're not pretty.

429
00:34:36,446 --> 00:34:44,160
And I'm sorry for getting the lead role
instead of you.

430
00:34:45,946 --> 00:34:47,660
Actually,

431
00:34:47,660 --> 00:34:52,146
we both should've been the female leads,
don't you think?

432
00:34:52,146 --> 00:34:56,226
But there can only be one female lead
in the play, right?

433
00:34:57,233 --> 00:35:00,573
One day, Snow White found some magic water.

434
00:35:00,573 --> 00:35:05,840
When she drank it,
something amazing happened!

435
00:35:09,740 --> 00:35:12,427
She found her other self.

436
00:35:12,427 --> 00:35:14,760
Wow!

437
00:35:17,100 --> 00:35:21,113
Suddenly, the magic water appears?
Are you sure that's a good idea?

438
00:35:21,113 --> 00:35:23,000
It doesn't have to be good.

439
00:35:23,000 --> 00:35:26,453
As long as the cast is having fun,
the audience will enjoy it too.

440
00:36:21,700 --> 00:36:24,473
Here. This is your new mask.

441
00:36:24,473 --> 00:36:28,840
I'm so nervous.
Am I really going to do well?

442
00:36:28,840 --> 00:36:30,760
It'll be fine.

443
00:36:31,913 --> 00:36:36,233
As long as the cast is having fun,
the audience will enjoy it too.

444
00:36:40,060 --> 00:36:41,860
Come on.

445
00:38:33,006 --> 00:38:36,139
Solar, who's your acting partner?

446
00:38:36,139 --> 00:38:38,367
He doesn't look familiar.

447
00:38:38,367 --> 00:38:41,213
Oh, he's a friend from another faculty.

448
00:38:42,713 --> 00:38:45,146
You two are just friends?

449
00:38:45,146 --> 00:38:47,126
We're really just friends.

450
00:38:49,100 --> 00:38:51,753
Alright, if you say so.

451
00:38:51,753 --> 00:38:54,867
Let's give the stage to the next pair.

452
00:38:54,867 --> 00:38:56,667
Thank you.

453
00:39:05,193 --> 00:39:06,761
We did it!

454
00:39:07,539 --> 00:39:10,433
I'm so glad I asked you to act with me.

455
00:39:15,600 --> 00:39:17,586
Is something wrong?

456
00:39:17,586 --> 00:39:19,746
No, I'm fine.

457
00:39:19,746 --> 00:39:21,199
What do you mean you're fine?

458
00:39:21,199 --> 00:39:24,039
You clearly look like a sad puppy.

459
00:39:29,633 --> 00:39:35,740
Well, you made it clear to the professor
that we're just friends.

460
00:39:47,573 --> 00:39:49,373
Pobmek.

461
00:39:53,860 --> 00:39:55,740
I trusted you today.

462
00:39:58,347 --> 00:40:03,393
I trusted you to act in the scene with me
as a friend.

463
00:40:04,613 --> 00:40:06,426
From now on,

464
00:40:07,353 --> 00:40:09,306
will you trust me too?

465
00:40:10,080 --> 00:40:11,940
Trust you with what?

466
00:40:15,113 --> 00:40:17,346
Well...

467
00:40:17,346 --> 00:40:22,047
Trust me to take care of you...
as your boyfriend.

468
00:40:22,047 --> 00:40:23,686
Huh?

469
00:40:23,686 --> 00:40:25,486
Boyfriend?

470
00:41:08,240 --> 00:41:10,040
Hey.

471
00:41:11,599 --> 00:41:14,340
I thought you said you're just friends.

472
00:41:15,027 --> 00:41:17,240
We were just friends a moment ago.

473
00:41:21,153 --> 00:41:23,133
But now we're boyfriends.

474
00:41:54,033 --> 00:41:56,946
You did amazing today, little director.

475
00:42:00,140 --> 00:42:01,618
Here.

476
00:42:03,233 --> 00:42:05,040
A lollipop again.

477
00:42:07,059 --> 00:42:09,606
What do you want then?

478
00:42:09,606 --> 00:42:11,733
You can ask for anything.

479
00:42:11,733 --> 00:42:14,179
Today's an exception.

480
00:42:14,179 --> 00:42:15,566
Really? Anything at all?

481
00:42:15,566 --> 00:42:17,366
Try asking.

482
00:42:25,000 --> 00:42:27,560
[Drop off Your "My Dream" Assignment]

483
00:42:30,700 --> 00:42:34,493
I want to go to the beach.
I've never been there before.

484
00:42:34,493 --> 00:42:36,293
Can I go?

485
00:42:45,419 --> 00:42:47,113
I've already signed it.

486
00:42:47,113 --> 00:42:48,933
I'll take you there.

487
00:42:52,120 --> 00:42:53,560
- Really?
- Yup.

488
00:42:53,560 --> 00:42:54,878
- You're not lying, are you?
- No.

489
00:42:54,878 --> 00:42:56,386
- Are you sure?
- Yeah.

490
00:42:56,386 --> 00:42:57,707
Yay!

491
00:42:57,707 --> 00:43:00,140
Love you as big as the world, Teacher!

492
00:43:09,740 --> 00:43:13,746
I'm glad you and Aurora made up.

493
00:43:13,746 --> 00:43:16,219
It's all thanks to Sun.

494
00:43:16,219 --> 00:43:18,019
Sun?

495
00:43:19,152 --> 00:43:22,433
The friend who said you're not pretty?
Which one is that?

496
00:43:22,433 --> 00:43:24,526
This one.

497
00:43:26,127 --> 00:43:27,240
Wait.

498
00:43:27,240 --> 00:43:29,320
Isn't this Teacher Solar?

499
00:43:29,320 --> 00:43:33,346
No, it's Sun, not Teacher Solar.

500
00:43:47,260 --> 00:43:50,979
Come on, Teacher Jee! Stop wiping it off.

501
00:43:50,979 --> 00:43:53,033
Aren't you going to eat?

502
00:43:54,187 --> 00:43:59,247
Honestly, I was worried
the play wouldn't turn out well,

503
00:43:59,247 --> 00:44:02,073
since it's not how we expected it to be.

504
00:44:02,073 --> 00:44:06,160
But seeing the kids happy
was a nice surprise.

505
00:44:07,353 --> 00:44:09,887
That's because you care about the kids
more than the work.

506
00:44:09,887 --> 00:44:11,687
That's it.

507
00:44:12,380 --> 00:44:14,313
Wow.

508
00:44:14,313 --> 00:44:18,346
My friend is in Mr. Moral Teacher mode.

509
00:44:19,160 --> 00:44:22,026
What's wrong with you? Just eat!

510
00:44:23,840 --> 00:44:25,460
Let's eat.

511
00:44:25,460 --> 00:44:29,609
By the way,
when I was helping Sun carry the paint,

512
00:44:29,609 --> 00:44:31,246
I found this.

513
00:44:31,246 --> 00:44:33,106
Give me a second.

514
00:44:34,793 --> 00:44:36,593
Here!

515
00:44:37,513 --> 00:44:38,840
Here.

516
00:44:38,840 --> 00:44:42,327
Why don't you practice with this,
so you can play it for Sun?

517
00:44:42,327 --> 00:44:45,946
Maybe it can replace the CD you broke.

518
00:44:48,480 --> 00:44:51,307
You were such a pro at playing the guitar.

519
00:44:51,307 --> 00:44:52,933
Why did you quit?

520
00:44:52,933 --> 00:44:55,453
I was hoping we could play as a duo.

521
00:44:59,553 --> 00:45:02,713
Hey, you guys still haven't left?

522
00:45:04,320 --> 00:45:05,580
Not yet.

523
00:45:05,580 --> 00:45:09,019
Come on, Solar. The pot is still hot.

524
00:45:09,019 --> 00:45:10,819
Thank you.

525
00:45:14,906 --> 00:45:17,426
How was the play?

526
00:45:17,426 --> 00:45:18,433
Did it go okay?

527
00:45:18,433 --> 00:45:21,100
It went way better than okay.

528
00:45:21,100 --> 00:45:23,619
Sun was really amazing, you know?

529
00:45:23,619 --> 00:45:27,746
So... does that mean I'm getting a reward?

530
00:45:33,407 --> 00:45:35,233
Hey.

531
00:45:35,233 --> 00:45:37,080
No. Too many people.

532
00:45:37,080 --> 00:45:40,300
Kiss! Kiss! Kiss!

533
00:45:40,300 --> 00:45:46,193
Kiss! Kiss!

534
00:45:46,193 --> 00:45:48,253
Aw!

535
00:45:48,253 --> 00:45:51,620
What?
That's not enough to make a BL girl happy.

536
00:45:51,620 --> 00:45:53,946
No! I'm shy!

537
00:45:53,946 --> 00:45:55,400
Too many people!

538
00:45:55,400 --> 00:45:58,560
- Just eat!
- Kiss again! Kiss again!

539
00:45:58,560 --> 00:46:00,860
Kiss again!

540
00:46:00,860 --> 00:46:02,460
Kiss again! Kiss again!

541
00:46:02,460 --> 00:46:04,400
- Kiss again!
- No way!

542
00:46:04,400 --> 00:46:05,715
Alright, enough.

543
00:46:08,349 --> 00:46:09,246
Let's just eat. Just eat.

544
00:46:09,246 --> 00:46:11,980
Don't let me find out
you two kiss behind our backs.

545
00:46:11,980 --> 00:46:13,986
Who's going to eat that now?

546
00:46:16,359 --> 00:46:18,987
This is Teacher Solar, isn't it?

547
00:46:18,987 --> 00:46:20,000
Why?

548
00:46:20,000 --> 00:46:23,073
I'd like to have a little chat with him.

549
00:46:23,073 --> 00:46:26,147
Take Solar home! Now!

550
00:46:26,147 --> 00:46:27,713
- Go!
- Solar!

551
00:46:28,473 --> 00:46:29,493
Sun, let's go!

552
00:46:29,493 --> 00:46:30,773
What?

553
00:46:32,473 --> 00:46:35,000
I can't get up. Help me.

554
00:46:35,000 --> 00:46:36,360
[Kiss Voucher - 1 kiss/hour]

555
00:46:36,507 --> 00:46:38,706
Are you really going to use it here?

